{
  "texts": [
    "Intervention providers are asked to not disclose group assignment to participants and assessors such as not talking about the mHealth intervention.",
    "Statisticians will receive data with unlabeled group coding and labels will only be revealed after completion of statistical analyses and start of interpretation of results.",
    "Sample sizeThe primary outcome is the improvement of modifiable unhealthy lifestyles, with a reduction by at least one unhealthy lifestyle at 6 months considered a favorable outcome (coded 1) and any other outcome unfavorable (coded 0).",
    "According to a previous study, the prevalence of at least one unhealthy lifestyle in Chinese community residents is 89.6% [2,37].",
    "According to an analysis of the previous two survey waves of the CMEC, it is expected that 2 percent of the control group participants will achieve a favorable outcome."
  ]
}